Iterator vs Iterable vs Generator
Iterable  → object you can loop over (has __iter__)
            Examples: list, tuple, str, dict, set

Iterator  → object that produces values one at a time
            Has __iter__ AND __next__
            Examples: iter([1,2,3]), file object, zip

Generator → special iterator created with yield
            Automatically has __iter__ and __next__
            Examples: generator functions, generator expressions
